]0;nasrin@LAPTOP-F30RQ071 [01;34mfirst-network $[00m /./n[K[K[K[K./network.sh -h
[0;34mUsing docker and docker-compose[0m
Usage: 
  network.sh <Mode> [Flags]
    Modes:
      [0;32mprereq[0m - Install Fabric binaries and docker images
      [0;32mup[0m - Bring up Fabric orderer and peer nodes. No channel is created
      [0;32mup createChannel[0m - Bring up fabric network with one channel
      [0;32mcreateChannel[0m - Create and join a channel after the network is created
      [0;32mdeployCC[0m - Deploy a chaincode to a channel (defaults to asset-transfer-basic)
      [0;32mcc[0m - chaincode functions, use "network.sh cc -h" for options
      [0;32mdown[0m - Bring down the network

    Flags:
    Used with [0;32mnetwork.sh prereq[0m
    -i     FabricVersion (default: '2.5.9')
    -cai   Fabric CA Version (default: '1.5.12')

    Used with [0;32mnetwork.sh up[0m, [0;32mnetwork.sh createChannel[0m:
    -ca - Use Certificate Authorities to generate network crypto material
    -cfssl <use CFSSL> -  Use CFSSL CA to generate network crypto material
    -bft - Use Orderers with consensus type BFT (Not available in Fabric v2.x)
    -c <channel name> - Name of channel to create (defaults to "mychannel")
    -s <dbtype> - Peer state database to deploy: goleveldb (default) or couchdb
    -r <max retry> - CLI times out after certain number of attempts (defaults to 5)
    -d <delay> - CLI delays for a certain number of seconds (defaults to 3)
    -verbose - Verbose mode

    Used with [0;32mnetwork.sh deployCC[0m:
    -c <channel name> - Name of channel to deploy chaincode to
    -ccn <name> - Chaincode name.
    -ccl <language> - Programming language of the chaincode to deploy: go, java, javascript, typescript
    -ccv <version>  - Chaincode version. 1.0 (default), v2, version3.x, etc
    -ccs <sequence>  - Chaincode definition sequence.  Must be auto (default) or an integer, 1 , 2, 3, etc
    -ccp <path>  - File path to the chaincode.
    -ccep <policy>  - (Optional) Chaincode endorsement policy using signature policy syntax. The default policy requires an endorsement from Org1 and Org2
    -cccg <collection-config>  - (Optional) File path to private data collections configuration file
    -cci <fcn name>  - (Optional) Name of chaincode initialization function. When a function is provided, the execution of init will be requested and the function will be invoked.

    -h - Print this message

 Possible Mode and flag combinations
   [0;32mup[0m -ca -r -d -s -verbose
   [0;32mup[0m -bft -r -d -s -verbose
   [0;32mup createChannel[0m -ca -c -r -d -s -verbose
   [0;32mup createChannel[0m -bft -c -r -d -s -verbose
   [0;32mcreateChannel[0m -bft -c -r -d -verbose
   [0;32mdeployCC[0m -ccn -ccl -ccv -ccs -ccp -cci -r -d -verbose

 Examples:
   network.sh up createChannel -ca -c mychannel -s couchdb
   network.sh createChannel -c channelName
   network.sh deployCC -ccn basic -ccp ../asset-transfer-basic/chaincode-javascript/ -ccl javascript
   network.sh deployCC -ccn mychaincode -ccp ./user/mychaincode -ccv 1 -ccl javascript

 NOTE: Default settings can be changed in network.config
